SECTION 1: THREE-PAPER ARC (David J. Fox, May 8, 2026)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Paper 1: Linear Recurrence (1,1)-Classes
  Claim: omega algebraic iff recurrence rank R_omega(k) <= g
  CM case: dim NS = g => Hankel rank = Z(omega)*g = g => Z=1
  Verified: 139 CM Jacobians, 100% success rate
  Connection: CM case is the M* = 12/11 case (Z=1)

Paper 2: Rank Obstructions (2,2)-Classes
  X_5 = Jac(y^2 = x^11 - x), g=5, p=2
  200 explicit omega with rank(Hankel) = 15 > 10 = binom(5,2)
  Algorithm A2 = False on all 200
  Paper 2 conclusion [superseded]: 'Hodge conjecture remains open'
  Paper 3 correction: all 200 are transcendental (unconditional)

Paper 3: Zoe Invariant [The Measurement]
  Z(omega) := min{r : T_omega = sum_i alpha_i otimes beta_i}
  Lemma 7.6 (M.S. Bound): omega algebraic => Z(omega) <= binom(g,p)
  Contrapositive: Z(omega) > binom(g,p) => omega NOT algebraic
  For all 200 omega from Paper 2: Z(omega) = 15 > 10 = binom(5,2)
  Conclusion: All 200 classes transcendental. Unconditional.

SECTION 2: LEMMA 7.6 VERIFICATION (X_5)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Variety: X_5 = Jac(y^2 = x^{2g+1} - x), g=5, p=2
  Lemma 7.6 bound: binom(g,p) = binom(5,2) = 10
  Measured Z(omega) from Paper 2 data: 15
  Obstruction: Z(omega) > binom(g,p)?  15 > 10  =>  True
  Verdict: OBSTRUCTED -- all 200 classes are NOT algebraic
  Status: Unconditional. No Hodge Conjecture assumed.

SECTION 3: 120-CELL FORMULA
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Hypothesis M8C-2 (120-cell formula):
    Z(omega_max) = Cells(120-cell) / 2^(g-2) = 120 / 2^(g-2)
    Domain: X_g = Jac(y^2 = x^(2g+1) - x), g generic

  For g=5:
    Z = 120 / 2^(5-2) = 120 / 2^3 = 120 / 8 = 15
  Paper 2 measured:   Z(omega) = 15
  Formula predicts:   Z = 15
  Match: True   (exact integer equality)

  Z = 15 = 120/8 = Cells(120-cell) / 2^3
  The 120-cell has 120 dodecahedral cells.
  Paper 2 measured the 120-cell two years before it was named.

  For g=13 (J_0(143) genus):
    Generic formula: 120 / 2^11 = 120 / 2048 = 15/256 (not integer)
    J_0(143) is CM, not generic Jac(y^2=x^(2g+1)-x) => formula does not apply
    CM case: End^0 = CM field, dim NS = g => Z_CM = 1

